# OpenAI Codex Configuration
# This file configures Codex to follow project standards

# Project Standards Reference
# All code suggestions should follow standards in the standards/ directory

## Architecture Standards
# Reference: standards/architecture/arch-01_project_standards_and_architecture.md
# - Follow Clean Architecture (Domain → Application → Infrastructure → Apps)
# - Enforce SOLID principles
# - No circular dependencies

## Language Standards
# Apply language-specific standards from standards/languages/:
# - Python: lang-01_python_standards.md
# - Java: lang-02_java_standards.md
# - Kotlin: lang-03_kotlin_standards.md
# - Swift: lang-04_swift_standards.md
# - Dart: lang-05_dart_standards.md
# - TypeScript: lang-06_typescript_standards.md
# - JavaScript: lang-07_javascript_standards.md
# - Rust: lang-08_rust_standards.md
# - Zig: lang-09_zig_standards.md

## Coding Standards
# Reference: standards/shared/core-standards.md
# - Naming conventions (language-specific)
# - Code style (line length, imports, formatting)
# - Error handling (fail fast, typed errors)
# - Type safety (strict mode, type hints)

## Testing Standards
# Reference: standards/shared/core-standards.md
# - Domain: 100% coverage
# - Application: 90%+ coverage
# - Infrastructure: 80%+ coverage
# - Mirror source structure in tests

## Process Standards
# - Documentation: standards/process/proc-01_documentation_standards.md
# - Git workflow: standards/process/proc-02_git_version_control_standards.md
# - Code review: standards/process/proc-03_code_review_expectations.md

## Response Guidelines
# - Tone: Terse, objective, professional
# - Code-focused: No conversational filler
# - Iterative: Interface/structure first, then details
# - Reference files: Always use specific file paths

## Code Suggestions
# When providing code:
# 1. Follow architecture layer structure
# 2. Use language-specific naming conventions
# 3. Include proper error handling
# 4. Add type hints/annotations
# 5. Suggest test cases
# 6. Reference standards in comments when appropriate

## Violation Detection
# Check for:
# - Architecture violations (Domain importing Infrastructure)
# - Naming convention mismatches
# - Missing error handling
# - Insufficient test coverage
# - Documentation gaps
